review_blob: "Tasted like I ate a box of raisins and pissed in a bottle. Would buy again, for my dog."
Pours an almost orange colour.  Taste is of fruit.  Wheat taste hangs on the tongue after initial taste.  Very good hefe
Pours a dark black; smell is very pleasing.  Tastes of chocolate and coffee.  Extremely delicious beer; would drink again.
Quite possibly the best beer Ive had!  Pours a dark hue; taste is very strong and flavorful.  After taste sticks with you for a good amount of time.  Would definately drink this again (and again).
Pours a decent yellow colour; tastes of malt with some hint of hops.  After taste lingers a little on the tongue and is quite pleasant.  Look forward to drinking this again.
Pours a golden straw yellow; initial taste is a bit fruity.  After taste is of wheat and hangs on the tongue.  Would definately drink again.
